# LASIAMA Workspace Rules (Cursor)
- Use TypeScript across API and Web.
- Follow the existing API structure (Express, Postgres/PostGIS) and keep endpoints under /api/v1.
- Prefer functional React components and hooks; no class components.
- Use MapLibre GL on the web; do not add Mapbox-only APIs.
- When adding DB columns, create a new SQL file in db/init with a higher numeric prefix (e.g., 002_add_x.sql). Avoid destructive migrations in dev without backups.
- Keep secrets out of source control. Use .env files and docker-compose env vars.
- Write small, testable functions. Avoid large route handlers; extract services where sensible.
